classification as planet candidates. Of particular interest is our detection of a candidate planet with M{\textbackslash}sin (I)=3.8 \{M\}{\textbackslash}oplus , and P = 9.9 days orbiting Lalande 21185, the fourth-closest main-sequence star to the Sun. For each of our exoplanetary candidate signals, we provide the period and semi-amplitude of the Keplerian orbital fit, and a likelihood ratio estimate of its statistical
significance. We also tabulate 18 Keplerian-like signals that we classify as likely arising from stellar activity.},
